<L>__{interior pie shop day}
<A>__{mrs. lovett is pouring toby a glass of gin, not his first. he gulps down the gin between ravenous bites of another meat pie as she nervously glances up to the ceiling, wondering what the hell is going on up there.}
<C>__{mrs. lovett}
<D>__{you ought to slow down a bit, lad. it'll go to your head.}
<C>__{toby}
<D>__{weaned on the stuff, i was. they used to give it to us at the workhouse, so's we could sleep. not that you'd ever want to sleep in that place, ma'am. not with the things wot happen in the dark.}
<C>__{mrs. lovett}
<D>__{that's nice, dear ... i think i will just pop in on mr. todd for a tick. you'll be all right here?}
<C>__{toby}
<D>__{leave the bottle.}
<A>__{she goes.}
